	<section class="page">
<p>Two of the world’s most widely used online storage services, <a href="https://help.dropbox.com/installs-integrations/desktop/macos-12-monterey-support" rel="noopener nofollow" target="_blank">Dropbox</a>, and <a href="https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-onedrive-blog/inside-the-new-files-on-demand-experience-on-macos/bc-p/3066588" rel="noopener nofollow" target="_blank">Microsoft</a> OneDrive, are <a href="https://help.dropbox.com/installs-integrations/desktop/macos-12-monterey-support" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">warning Mac users</a> of a looming problem in a coming macoS Monterey update.</p><h2><strong>You’ll need to download files to use them for a while</strong></h2>
<p>They warn that some users may have problems when attempting to open files stored in either service using another Mac application. They urge customers to update their apps once macOS 12.3 is installed.</p><p class="jumpTag"><a href="/article/3648044/dropbox-microsoft-onedrive-send-out-warnings-to-macos-users.html#jump">To read this article in full, please click here</a></p></section></article>